<span class="postbody">It sounds like the original poster went into Fear without a Feign Death-capable player who knows Fear geography going in first and training a bunch of monsters away from the zone-in.  Fear isn't that difficult if you do that first.  Otherwise, with some bad luck, you can have a dozen or more in camp when you get there, with a few more incoming as they die.
<br />

<br />
However, many folks (like me) prefer the helter skelter break-in for the Crowd Control fun!  If you're in a 46-55 raid with little or no prior experience in Fear, I would recommend the FD train tactic though!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
